Hopefully some of the shops are open. <</if>> [[Continue|downtown2]]Following the path from the gondola, I find myself in a large circular plaza. Probably a marketplace or park in years past, the plaza now rests as a lifeless entryway to the winding streets of Trout's Mouth. With all of this space, I can only imagine what it would have looked like in its prime. There’s even a small bandstand for live performers. It mostly feels sad now. A lot of care went into making this a communal space. Near the bandstand lies a pathway that leads out of the town's center, winding back towards the coast. Before it sits a sign which reads "Scenic Overlook" The only building in the center that isn’t boarded up or hollowed out is a cozy looking joint with a swinging wooden sign. It’s very worn down, so I can barely make out the word “Hammond’s Place.” <<if $knowhammonds>> This must be the place Oswald mentioned. <<else>> The sign on the door simply reads “Inn.” <</if>>
